The bachelor students will participate in seminars recommended by their supervisor. Additionally, students will learn to find, read and interpret scientific text and will eventually give an oral presentation based on the literature. 
The venue, time and public of presentation will be assigned in agreement with the supervisor and the head of chair. In general, the presentation should be given in Estonian, but exceptions can be made based on well-founded reasons (in agreement with the supervisor and the head of chair). 
If possible, students will be introduced to other research topics of the workgroup and/or participate to some extent in the lab or fieldworks of the team.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Bachelor students will become familiar with the current topics relating to student's specialty and students will develop the reading skills of scientific literature. Students will learn searching scientific literature from databases and the correct interpretation of scientific text. Students will develop their presentation skills on scientific topics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who has passed the subject: - knows the most important problems and research questions related to his / her speciality; - can search for information in scientific databases; - distinguishes the most important content of a research article from a less important one; - expresses himself / herself intelligibly in Estonian or English both orally and in writing - communicates with his/her team members, participates in discussions and practical teamwork; - reflects what he / she has learned during the course in both oral and written form; - understands his / her strengths and weaknesses and is able to build up study motivation and better plan the writing of a bachelor's thesis.
